a-and I'm gonna make
a Valentine for my mom.

10:51.266 --> 10:54.001
They're not the same!

10:54.068 --> 10:55.653
Okay, open --
open mine first.

10:55.721 --> 10:57.037
Oh.
It's -- It's a kimono.

10:57.105 --> 10:59.106
I took an online
origami class.

10:59.174 --> 11:01.091
Okay.
It's a haiku.

11:01.159 --> 11:03.343
Oh!
"Friend, lover, husband.

11:03.411 --> 11:05.479
My life started
when we met.

11:05.547 --> 11:06.914
You're my everything."

11:06.982 --> 11:08.015
Aww.
You are.

11:08.083 --> 11:10.184
Ooh, let's see what you wrote
in yours.

11:10.252 --> 11:12.320
Aww.
It's a tandem bicycle.

11:12.387 --> 11:14.004
Yeah.
It's so cute.

11:14.072 --> 11:15.923
"Happy V-Day.

11:15.991 --> 11:17.358
Love, M."

11:17.426 --> 11:18.859
And I thought my date
was cold.

11:18.927 --> 11:21.395
What? No.
Cam knows what I mean.

11:21.463 --> 11:23.464
Cam knows
you <i> are</i> mean?

11:23.531 --> 11:24.948
You were more effusive
about tonight's menu

11:24.967 --> 11:26.517
than you were
in my card.

11:26.584 --> 11:28.602
"The molten
chocolate cake looks
slutty and delicious."

11:28.670 --> 11:30.505
Would it kill you
to say that about me?

11:30.572 --> 11:32.306
What the hell?
Amanda <i> was</i> here.

11:32.373 --> 11:33.958
This picture you posted
on Facebook --

11:34.026 --> 11:37.878
She's right behind you.
Why would she just leave?

11:39.197 --> 11:40.665
Tonight was supposed to be
a romantic night.

11:40.715 --> 11:42.533
I don't want to watch Luke
make his sweaty moves

11:42.600 --> 11:43.834
on his conquest
of the week.

11:43.902 --> 11:45.269
Yeah,
and some of them buy it.

11:45.337 --> 11:46.504
Under what gas leak is

11:46.555 --> 11:48.739
he finding these
brain-dead bimbos?

11:48.807 --> 11:50.357
I know what happened.

11:50.425 --> 11:52.743
She walked in,
saw me for the first time,

11:52.811 --> 11:54.162
and thought I was hideous.

11:54.229 --> 11:56.213
I've really been struggling
with my hair lately.

11:56.281 --> 11:58.533
No, no, stop it.
You have great hair.

11:58.600 --> 12:00.751
If it worked
for Sheena Easton,
it can work for you.

12:00.819 --> 12:02.536
We spent
all this time texting.

12:02.604 --> 12:03.871
I thought we had
a real connection,

12:03.939 --> 12:06.891
like, we really got
each other.

12:06.958 --> 12:08.375
We couldn't let him
blame himself.

12:08.427 --> 12:10.545
But, uh...he took it
pretty well.

12:10.612 --> 12:11.929
You catty bitches!

12:11.997 --> 12:15.466
Luke, we love you,
but ever since
you hit puberty,

12:15.533 --> 12:17.834
you've been...
a little disgusting.
A little disgusting.

12:17.886 --> 12:19.637
Don't you think
I know that?!

12:19.705 --> 12:21.622
She was my chance
to turn it around.

12:21.690 --> 12:22.989
Okay, you know what?
Call her.

12:23.057 --> 12:24.741
We'll get on the phone,
we'll clear
the whole thing up.

12:24.809 --> 12:26.477
I called her.
She's not picking up.

12:26.544 --> 12:28.112
We're going
to her apartment.

12:28.179 --> 12:30.014
We messed this up,
we'll fix it.

12:30.082 --> 12:31.582
Before the cake arrives?

12:31.649 --> 12:33.917
I've been wanting
to bury my face
in that all night long.

12:33.986 --> 12:35.920
How can you not
hear this?

12:35.954 --> 12:38.105
Okay, Joey,
it's getting late.

12:38.173 --> 12:40.274
It's time to get you
up to bed.

12:40.342 --> 12:43.044
Can you do a quick
monster check first?

12:43.111 --> 12:45.479
Yes, I can.

12:47.665 --> 12:50.251
Phil, I can't sleep
without my teddy bear,

12:50.318 --> 12:52.270
and I left him
in my wagon.

12:52.337 --> 12:55.206
Can you get him?
I'm afraid of the dark.

12:55.273 --> 12:57.124
You got it, buddy.

13:00.361 --> 13:02.629
Joe?
What are you doing?

13:02.697 --> 13:04.448
Open the door.

13:04.516 --> 13:06.534
Fulgencio Joseph
Pritchett!

13:06.551 --> 13:07.885
Open the door!

13:09.837 --> 13:12.039
You let me in right now,
young man.

13:12.074 --> 13:14.091
Hey.
Not cool, Joe!

13:18.980 --> 13:22.733
Joe, what is going on
with this music?

13:22.801 --> 13:23.718
My God.

13:23.785 --> 13:25.319
Oh.
Where's Phil?

13:25.387 --> 13:28.005
Who knows
with that guy?

13:30.341 --> 13:31.808
Honey, what happened?

13:31.876 --> 13:33.811
Mini Casanova
locked me out.

13:33.879 --> 13:35.996
What?
That is enough.

13:36.064 --> 13:37.931
Joe, you are
a little boy,

13:37.999 --> 13:40.467
and you're going to bed
right now.

13:40.552 --> 13:43.304
You're a bad Valentine!

13:45.257 --> 13:46.957
Oh, no.

13:47.008 --> 13:48.476
I feel like the rest
of the Breakfast Club

13:48.543 --> 13:50.194
when they realized
Judd Nelson was

13:50.262 --> 13:52.980
more vulnerable
than they thought.
I...

13:53.047 --> 13:56.017
My hotel
in Ibiza was my favorite.

13:56.084 --> 13:57.934
I used to hang out
with Telly Savalas,

13:57.953 --> 13:59.353
Lyle Waggoner,

13:59.420 --> 14:01.305
but the scenery here

14:01.373 --> 14:03.807
makes me like this one
mucho more.

14:03.875 --> 14:06.143
You don't have to impress me
with money

14:06.211 --> 14:08.729
or name-dropping,
I think.

14:08.797 --> 14:09.996
I like you.

14:10.064 --> 14:11.298
Don't tell this
to my madam,

14:11.366 --> 14:14.267
but I cannot accept
any money from you.

14:14.335 --> 14:15.386
Excuse me, ma'am.

14:15.420 --> 14:16.637
Can I talk with you
for a moment?

14:19.958 --> 14:21.475
Yes?

14:21.543 --> 14:23.210
I'm gonna have to ask you
to leave now.

14:23.212 --> 14:24.411
Huh?

14:24.479 --> 14:25.863
The hotel owner
is very strict about...

14:25.930 --> 14:27.948
women who
do what you do.

14:28.016 --> 14:30.418
Ooh, you're gonna
take me to a room

14:30.485 --> 14:32.953
where the hotel owner
is going to give me

14:33.021 --> 14:35.389
a very tough,
sexy talking to?

14:35.456 --> 14:37.992
No, you're gonna leave,
or we're gonna
call the police.

14:38.059 --> 14:39.543
Yes, call the police.
Gloria --

14:39.611 --> 14:42.162
I've been a very, very
bad girl.

14:42.230 --> 14:43.597
This is not a part of it.

14:43.665 --> 14:46.517
Sir, she is not
a prostitute.

14:47.235 --> 14:48.502
This is my wife.

14:48.536 --> 14:50.003
That's what
they all say.

14:50.071 --> 14:50.955
Please.

14:51.973 --> 14:54.508
Yep, that's probably what
I would've said.

14:56.678 --> 14:58.245
Here she is.
Ciconi.

14:59.681 --> 15:01.031
What do you want?

15:01.099 --> 15:01.832
Oh, hi!
Here she is.

15:02.000 --> 15:03.467
Hey! Wow.

15:03.535 --> 15:04.918
You're actually hotter
than your picture.

15:04.986 --> 15:07.387
You know, let us talk.
Hi! So, we're --

15:07.455 --> 15:08.889
we're Luke's uncles.
We're Luke's uncles.

15:08.956 --> 15:10.658
- You're his uncles?
- Uh-huh.

15:10.809 --> 15:13.460
And you said he puts sweaty
moves on brain-dead bimbos?

15:13.528 --> 15:14.945
Okay, hadn't heard
the specifics.

15:15.013 --> 15:16.330
Okay, you know --
you know what?

15:16.398 --> 15:17.848
We d-- We didn't mean
any of that.

15:17.916 --> 15:19.917
We're gay,
and gays are snarky.

15:19.984 --> 15:21.101
It's a cultural thing.

15:21.169 --> 15:22.619
You know how, like,
you're Italian?

15:22.687 --> 15:24.572
Italians talk
a lot with their hands, right?

15:24.639 --> 15:25.673
And are much looser

15:25.741 --> 15:26.890
than one would imagine
for Catholics.

15:26.958 --> 15:28.108
Okay, okay.
Let me talk right now.

15:28.176 --> 15:30.878
Okay, Amanda,
Luke's an amazing guy.

15:30.946 --> 15:32.045
Why would I believe
what you're saying now

15:32.113 --> 15:33.897
and not what
you said before?

15:33.965 --> 15:35.115
I don't know.
I don't know.

15:35.250 --> 15:36.650
You know, maybe we were
just being snarky

15:36.718 --> 15:38.835
because we were jealous
of you guys.
Yeah.

15:38.903 --> 15:40.637
I mean, seeing Luke
all dressed up,

15:40.705 --> 15:42.389
getting ready
for a first date, the --

15:42.457 --> 15:45.209
the excitement of being
young and in love.

15:45.276 --> 15:46.893
Mm.
Easy.

15:46.961 --> 15:49.045
I-I remember when
I first met Cam --

15:49.097 --> 15:50.297
I'm Cam.
This is Cam.

15:50.365 --> 15:52.049
I knew I had met
the person

15:52.117 --> 15:54.468
I was gonna spend
the rest of my life with.

15:54.535 --> 15:57.070
That's what I want, too --
a relationship,

15:57.138 --> 15:58.756
someone who's gonna
be there for me.

15:58.824 --> 15:59.907
Luke feels
the same way.

15:59.974 --> 16:02.943
I mean, this is a guy
who is ready for commitment.

16:03.010 --> 16:04.411
We've really
only texted.

16:04.479 --> 16:05.612
Okay, well,
when I say --

16:05.680 --> 16:06.947
when I say
to give Luke a chance,

16:07.032 --> 16:09.599
it's because I-I know
what's at stake for you.

16:09.667 --> 16:11.868
I-I mean, you think
it's amazing now?

16:11.936 --> 16:15.322
You can't even imagine
what it could grow into.

16:15.389 --> 16:17.391
If you guys have
even the smallest chance

16:17.458 --> 16:20.711
of having what we have...
you have to go for it.

16:20.779 --> 16:21.995
Oh, my God, Mitchell.

16:22.063 --> 16:24.331
That is the Valentine's Day
card I've always wanted.

16:24.399 --> 16:25.883
Aww.

16:25.951 --> 16:27.618
That was sweet.

16:27.686 --> 16:28.919
But Luke's gone.

16:29.021 --> 16:30.638
Drive until
you hear a party.

16:30.705 --> 16:32.272
Okay. Well, you know what?
Good luck, honey.

16:32.391 --> 16:33.473
Bye, then.
Yeah, take care.

16:33.558 --> 16:34.725
Okay.

16:34.792 --> 16:36.960
You see? We have
the same address

16:37.028 --> 16:38.829
and the same last name.

16:38.897 --> 16:40.680
I was just pretending
to be a prostitute

16:40.765 --> 16:43.851
because my husband has a thing
for Jane Fonda in "Klute."

16:43.918 --> 16:44.952
The body was crazy,

16:45.020 --> 16:47.037
unfortunately,
so were the politics.

16:47.105 --> 16:49.005
Well, I guess you didn't do
anything wrong by hotel rules,

16:49.073 --> 16:51.942
but based on my personal
belief system --

16:52.010 --> 16:53.860
We're not looking for
any input. Thank you.

16:53.928 --> 16:55.979
I can't believe I took
romantic advice from Phil,

16:56.047 --> 16:59.550
a grown man I've seen in
lederhosen
at least three times.

17:00.785 --> 17:03.587
Phil told you to do
the role play?

17:03.654 --> 17:05.339
Yeah, he said you were mad
this morning

17:05.406 --> 17:07.624
because I always drop the ball
on days like this.

17:07.692 --> 17:09.159
I wasn't mad at you.

17:09.227 --> 17:12.444
I was mad at Joe
because he didn't make me
a Valentine.

17:12.512 --> 17:14.714
So, your 6-year-old kid
doesn't give you a card,

17:14.782 --> 17:16.901
you get so mad,
you throw a tire iron
through the windshield.

17:16.968 --> 17:18.602
It's got to be deeper
than that.

17:18.669 --> 17:20.020
Manny,
for the first time ever,

17:20.088 --> 17:21.872
didn't make me
a Valentine's, either.

17:21.940 --> 17:23.089
That's not deeper.

17:23.223 --> 17:26.926
That's just doubling down
on the same disturbing thing.

17:26.994 --> 17:27.777
Disturbing?

17:27.896 --> 17:29.246
When Manny was
5 years old,

17:29.314 --> 17:31.915
he told me that he would
forever be my Valentine's.

17:31.983 --> 17:35.402
Promises were made.
I will not be ignored!

17:37.222 --> 17:38.822
Okay, yeah.
That sounded weird.

17:38.890 --> 17:41.058
But the point is
that I know

17:41.125 --> 17:43.193
that you're not good
at romantic things,

17:43.261 --> 17:44.361
and I'm fine with it.

17:44.679 --> 17:47.014
Don't let me off the hook.
If I did more,

17:47.081 --> 17:49.516
you won't depend on your kids
for those things.

17:49.584 --> 17:51.001
And if I learned anything

17:51.069 --> 17:52.553
from trying to pick you up
tonight,

17:52.620 --> 17:54.104
it's how lucky
I was to get you
in the first place.

17:54.172 --> 17:55.606
I've got to do better.

17:56.174 --> 17:58.075
And I didn't think anyone

17:58.143 --> 18:01.545
could get any sexier
than Raoul Matadore.

18:04.682 --> 18:07.117
I want to remember
the exact moment

18:07.185 --> 18:09.620
I fell in love with you
all over again.

18:12.374 --> 18:13.957
What the hell
have you done?

18:14.025 --> 18:16.493
That was
my father's watch!

18:18.446 --> 18:20.030
Poor little Joe.

18:20.098 --> 18:22.283
You don't think I led him on,
do you?

18:22.350 --> 18:23.967
No, no.

18:24.035 --> 18:25.168
I am not doing this.

18:25.236 --> 18:26.987
Women always blame
themselves.

18:27.055 --> 18:29.290
Well, I'm sorry, Joe.
I don't owe you anything.

18:29.357 --> 18:32.509
You know what?
I-I think I'll handle this.

18:34.629 --> 18:35.912
Hey, buddy.

18:35.980 --> 18:38.181
Are you gonna yell
at me, too?

18:38.249 --> 18:39.449
Listen.

18:39.517 --> 18:41.184
The reason Claire
was yelling at you

18:41.252 --> 18:43.553
was to protect
my feelings.

18:43.621 --> 18:45.990
She knows I can't
compete with you,

18:46.057 --> 18:47.591
which is, um...

18:47.659 --> 18:50.477
which is why I have to ask you
a really big favor.

18:50.545 --> 18:52.713
Can you pick
another girl?

18:52.781 --> 18:54.598
I mean, you can have
anyone you want,

18:54.666 --> 18:57.001
but...
Claire's all I've got.

18:57.068 --> 18:58.969
I'd be lost without her.

18:59.037 --> 19:00.571
I don't even know how
I got her
in the first place.

19:00.638 --> 19:02.005
You <i> are</i> pretty silly.

19:02.073 --> 19:05.709
What do you say?
Dude to dude,
will you back off?

19:08.079 --> 19:09.846
Okay.

19:11.015 --> 19:12.316
Is Haley seeing anyone?

19:12.383 --> 19:13.350
Easy.

19:25.363 --> 19:27.981
How'd I get back to Arvin?
I don't know.

19:28.049 --> 19:29.466
I was just looking
for the parking lot

19:29.517 --> 19:31.368
when I came to a fork
in the path.

19:31.436 --> 19:32.736
Had I taken the other path,

19:32.803 --> 19:36.456
I would've just gotten
in my car
and gone home.

19:36.524 --> 19:38.058
Instead...

19:39.611 --> 19:41.661
You came back!

19:41.729 --> 19:43.631
Damn it, I did!

19:43.698 --> 19:46.116
Why did you run off?
What did I do?

19:46.251 --> 19:48.468
Everything.
And I've done nothing.

19:48.553 --> 19:50.437
I-I feel like a loser.

19:50.505 --> 19:51.805
<i>You</i> feel like a loser?

19:51.873 --> 19:55.476
Why do you think I went on
about myself so appallingly?

19:55.543 --> 19:56.977
Ooh, look at me.

19:57.045 --> 19:58.529
I won
the Von Snootington Award

19:58.596 --> 20:00.864
for Applied
Astro-Doofinomics.

20:00.932 --> 20:03.583
You won another award?
How is this helping?

20:03.651 --> 20:06.219
Haley...I like you.

20:07.004 --> 20:10.056
You are formidable
in a way that's...

20:11.275 --> 20:14.527
that's different
and exciting to me.

20:14.613 --> 20:16.396
Yeah, well, same,

20:16.463 --> 20:18.348
but it just doesn't
make sense.

20:18.416 --> 20:20.284
I love things that
don't make sense.

20:20.352 --> 20:22.168
That's my gig.

20:22.170 --> 20:24.188
Let's figure this out
together.

20:24.255 --> 20:25.572
Come on.

20:25.640 --> 20:27.057
What can I do?

20:33.447 --> 20:35.582
That helps.

20:40.706 --> 20:43.674
Oh, it's so weird to
think that if I had
taken another path,

20:43.742 --> 20:45.743
I could be heading home
right now.

20:45.810 --> 20:48.028
Wait a minute.
It's like what
you said before.

20:48.096 --> 20:51.564
In a different universe,
you could be
with someone else.

21:02.193 --> 21:05.045
Um, uh, could we --
could we change this song?

21:05.113 --> 21:06.513
The poppy cadence
is throwing off

21:06.580 --> 21:09.383
my more bluesy
lovemaking style.

21:09.450 --> 21:10.467
Oh!

21:10.535 --> 21:12.268
Aw, geez!
<i>Dios mio!</i>

21:12.336 --> 21:13.953
Don't you ever knock?!
This is my bedroom!

21:14.089 --> 21:16.540
I can't believe this is
happening again!

21:16.608 --> 21:17.891
Again?
Oh.

21:17.959 --> 21:19.142
I wish I had
gotten arrested!

21:19.210 --> 21:21.762
Mom, where are you?
I made you a Valen--

21:23.547 --> 21:26.383
Okay, what kind of freak show
goes on here
when I'm not around?

